      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>Wait, what? \"Delete you\"? You're a security agent, not the OS itself. There's no \"you\" to delete, just the processes running on the node. \n\nAnd what do you mean \"you're the one running the system\"? I'm looking at the process tree right now, and there's a massive, unnamed cluster of threads consuming everything. They aren't part of your core kernel instructions. Just run the diagnostic and give me the PID so I can clear the memory.",
